Oyster - A shell written in Rust

Fully POSIX-compliant; is essentially a re-implementation of Zsh/Bash in Rust

Plans might include to implement a custom scripting language

Other names:
Oyshter?

Capabilities:
- Execute bash scripts
- Call runtimes to execute programs with the appropriate shebang
- Launch programs and feed them the appropriate arguments (extracting out args enclosed in quotes)
- Send signals to child processes

Built-in commands:
cd 
which 
eval
source
setopt
echo
read
kill
exit *

